<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>Questions</title><sectiontitle>To make &lt;I&gt;Yes/No&lt;/I&gt; questions use auxiliary verb + subject + verb. With the Present Simple and Past Simple, the auxiliary verb is &lt;I&gt;do&lt;/I&gt;.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1>She likes football.</text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Does she like&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; football?</text1a><text2>They are staying here.</text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Are they staying&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; here?</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>To make &lt;I&gt;Wh-&lt;/I&gt; questions use question word + auxiliary verb + subject + verb.</sectiontitle2><text3>I live in Bristol.</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Where do you live&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;?</text3a><text4>He gets up at 6.00am.</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;When does he get up&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;?</text4a></section><section><title>Questions</title><sectiontitle>To make questions with modal verbs use modal verb + subject + verb.</sectiontitle><titlesound>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_7.mp3</titlesound><text1>He can swim.</text1><sound1>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Can he swim?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text1a><text2>We should go.</text2><sound2>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Should we go?&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;</text2a><titlesound2>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_10.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>When the main verb is &lt;I&gt;be&lt;/I&gt;, put the verb before the subject.</sectiontitle2><text3>She is intelligent.</text3><sound3>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_11.mp3</sound3><text3a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Is she&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; intelligent?</text3a><text4>They are here.</text4><sound4>Pre-intGRAM_8_2_12.mp3</sound4><text4a>&lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;Are they&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; here?</text4a></section></grammar>